@again4you You can firstly uninstall tensorflow or tensorflow-gpu, and grpcio, protobuf, which you installed via pip in the system.

For detailed reasons, the cmake script that uses python to generate some stuffs attempts to import system modules first, rather than your built version.

In addition, I also found a bug or a missing step when imports google.protobuf, I am trying to work it out later.
